In the Matter of George W. FORTIER, Bankrupt. Helen S. CREHORE v. George W. FORTIER, Bankrupt. No. 5465. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit June 27, 1935. Theodore G. Reiner and M. C. Eiseman, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Edward P. Madigan, of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before EVANS, FITZHENRY, and ALSCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
